Sentencas: The cobalt doped perovskite cathode material LaNi1-xCoxO3-delta (x = 0.4, 0.6, 0.8) synthesized by cost effective high temperature decomposition is investigated as mixed ionic electronic conductor (MIEC) for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of mixed ionic electronic perovskite cathode LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ for IT-SOFC synthesized by high temperature decomposition

Sentencas: LaNiO3 is known for its high electronic conductivity and to introduce more oxygen vacancies for enhancing its ionic conductivity, Ni at B site is substituted by Co. XRD analysis showed perovskite structure for all samples with no additional phases, which was also confirmed by FTIR results.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of mixed ionic electronic perovskite cathode LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ for IT-SOFC synthesized by high temperature decomposition

Sentencas: Microstructure analysis revealed well connected and porous structure for LaNi1-xCoxO3-delta (x = 0.6) compared to other compositions.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of mixed ionic electronic perovskite cathode LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ for IT-SOFC synthesized by high temperature decomposition

Sentencas: The elemental analysis using EDX confirmed presence of lanthanum, nickel, and cobalt within all samples.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of mixed ionic electronic perovskite cathode LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ for IT-SOFC synthesized by high temperature decomposition

Sentencas: No prominent weight loss was observed during TGA analysis.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of mixed ionic electronic perovskite cathode LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ for IT-SOFC synthesized by high temperature decomposition

Sentencas: The highest value of conductivity was obtained for LaNi1-xCoxO3-delta (x = 0.6) due to its porous and networked structure of sub micrometric grains.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of mixed ionic electronic perovskite cathode LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ for IT-SOFC synthesized by high temperature decomposition

Sentencas: The superior performance is attained for the cell based on LaNi1-xCoxO3-delta (x = 0.6) cathode with maximum power density of 0.45 Wcm(-2) compared to other composition which can be attributed to its well connected and porous structure that caused enhanced electrochemical reaction at triple phase boundary (TPB).
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of mixed ionic electronic perovskite cathode LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ for IT-SOFC synthesized by high temperature decomposition

Sentencas: It was therefore deduced that LaNi1-xCoxO3-delta (x = 0.6) is promising composition to be used as MIEC cathode for IT-SOFC.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of mixed ionic electronic perovskite cathode LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ for IT-SOFC synthesized by high temperature decomposition
